From: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7996: radar mis-attribution bug

Radar events are broadcast to all radios instead of attributed to the one that detected them.

Pass the detecting phy's channel context instead, so only the affected
band is marked. Fall back to NULL (current behaviour) if the phy has no
chanctx at the time of the event.

Signed-off-by: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
---
--- a/mt7996/mcu.c
+++ b/mt7996/mcu.c
@@ -791,10 +791,22 @@
 						&dev->rdd2_chandef,
 						GFP_ATOMIC);
 	} else {
+		struct ieee80211_chanctx_conf *conf = NULL;
 		struct mt7996_phy *phy = mphy->priv;
 
+		/* All bands share one wiphy: radar reported with a NULL
+		 * chanctx marks every channel context, so each BSS logs a
+		 * radar event at its own frequency (e.g. on 2.4 GHz where
+		 * no radar detector exists). Report it on the detecting
+		 * band's context only.
+		 */
+		if (mphy->chanctx)
+			conf = container_of((void *)mphy->chanctx,
+					    struct ieee80211_chanctx_conf,
+					    drv_priv);
+
 		phy->rdd_tx_paused = true;
-		ieee80211_radar_detected(mphy->hw, NULL);
+		ieee80211_radar_detected(mphy->hw, conf);
 	}
 	dev->hw_pattern++;
 
